[1] Switzerland (Neuchâtel)
Date: Wed 21 Feb 2018
Source: RTS [in French trans Corr.SB; edited]
https://www.rts.ch/info/regions/neuchatel/9353623-flambee-de-rougeole-avec-sept-cas-dans-le-canton-de-neuchatel.html


The canton of Neuchâtel is experiencing a measles outbreak. In one month, the Cantonal Public Health Service became aware of 7 cases of this contagious viral disease. Measures to keep children [that are not vaccinated] away have been declared.

On 18 Jan 2018, Vaud [canton] health authorities informed the Neuchâtel cantonal doctor of a case of measles in a 6 year old child who was residing in the canton of Vaud, but attending a Neuchâtel school. Despite control measures, 6 new cases were reported.

Those infected are 2 adults employed in a company and 4 young children attending a childcare facility. Vaud health authorities identified the people in contact with the sick child during the contagious period.

Those unvaccinated against measles were removed from the community for 21 days, the canton of Neuchâtel said on Wed 21 Feb 2018. This measure is necessary and must be applied as required by the law on epidemics. The cantonal doctor says that measles is one of the most contagious viral diseases.

