[3] Ireland (Limerick)
Date: Thu 22 Feb 2018 08:00 GMT
Source: The Liberal [edited]
http://theliberal.ie/hse-confirm-the-number-of-measles-cases-are-on-the-rise-in-limerick-as-15-cases-have-been-reported-in-the-city/


HSE [Health Service Executive] confirm the number of measles cases are on the rise in Limerick as 15 cases have been reported in the city. It is understood the announcement comes after the health authority revealed that 15 cases have been reported in the region since the beginning of the year [2018].

Although a disease outbreak control team has been sent to the region, the HSE are advising those living the region to make sure they are vaccinated in order to prevent further spread of the illness. In announcement made on its website the health authority revealed that many of the cases were reported in the Ballinacurra Weston and Carew Park area of the city. They also say those who have not been vaccinated should get vaccinated immediately.

[byline: Michael McKeowen]

